pf.graph
Interface Graph

All Known Subinterfaces:
Vertex
All Known Implementing Classes:
BoardGraph, GraphImpl, VertexImpl
public interface Graph

This represents a general graph. It contains subgraphs and vertices. All this is organized in a tree-like structure with vertices as leaves. Subgraphs are usually components of graph.

There are no methods for manipulating graph here. This works mainly as an entry point to graph. It has iterators over vertices and edges.

Parameter used mostly means a restriction to unused edges only.

Author:
Adam Juraszek
